Building qscript requires the following directory structure where qscript-0.11
is the top level directory:

/media/sda3/home/nxd/test/qscript-0.11
|-- bin
|-- cmake
|   `-- modules
|-- config
|-- include
|-- inputs
|-- lib
|-- make-build-dir
|   |-- compiletime_lib
|   |-- compiletime_static_lib
|   |-- runtime_lib
|   `-- runtime_static_lib
|-- resources
|-- src
`-- testsuite
    |-- config
    `-- qscript.test


The following command will build the compiler, but you need the following 
1. ncurses (with the development header files and library)
2. g++


1. Command to build the compiler

	make -f CustomQScriptMakefile local_install

2. Ensure that the bin directory contains "qscript"

3. Test the compiler
	$export QSCRIPT_HOME=`pwd`
	$cd input
	$../bin/qscript -n -f inp_jump_test

	compiler should generate inp_jump_test.C, inp_jump_test.exe

4.	Execute the generated file
	$LD_LIBARARY_PATH=$QSCRIPT_HOME/lib inp_jump_test.exe

